column.name: initial_page
column.Comment: The url for the landing page.

column.name: referer
column.Comment: The url that referred the user to the landing page.

column.name: date_landed
column.Comment: The date the landing page was hit.

column.name: ip
column.Comment: The IP address of the user who created the account. IPv4 (15 chars), IPv6 (39 chars) IPv6 notation for IPv4 (45 chars)

column.name: renewal_notice_email
column.Comment: Number of days before the expiration of certificates to send a renewal email

column.name: renewal_notice_phone
column.Comment: Number of days before the expiration of certificates to call to remind about renewal.

column.name: checklist_name_id
column.Comment: This column allows us to make rejection/other step status messages that are specific to a checklist_name_id. Excluding a checklist_name_id allows status codes to be reused across multiple checklists which all include some checklist_step_id where they all

column.name: customer_status_code
column.Comment: Allows the API to pass back standard 'reason codes' along with the status messages. Note that you could hypothetically have 2 messages with different message texts (customer_message) for human consumption, but whose semantic meaning for automated systems

column.name: checkbox_customer_status_id
column.Comment: A customer message (with optional API status code) for this checkmark. Currently used to include a customer-friendly "reject reason" for gTLD's.
